    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-10-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="181"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#center">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">[Telegram.</hi>—<date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1863-10-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 29, 1863</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Her Majesty’s Treasury</persName> to <persName type="to"
                        >Laird Brothers</persName>.</head>
                <p>From the Assistant Secretary, the Treasury, Whitehall, to Messrs. Laird,
                    Birkenhead.</p>
                <p>Captain Inglefield will, no doubt, in his dispositions regarding the iron-clad
                    vessels, take every proper precaution for the preservation of the property. The
                    orders have been well considered, and cannot be revoked or altered.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
